                                <collation>
                                    <p>There are 10 gatherings in the manuscript.</p>
                                </collation>
                                <condition>
                                    <p>There are several lacunae in the manuscript, which consists
                                        of 10 gatherings. I: There is a lacunae at the beginning.
                                        II: The gathering is complete. III: All the leaves are
                                        missing. IV: The 6th and 7th leaf are missing between the
                                        ff. 13v and 14r.V: The gathering, which consists of 4
                                        leaves, is intact. VI: Originally the gathering consisted of
                                        6 leaves, now 3 are missing between 27v and 28r. VIII:
                                        Originally the gathering consisted of 6 leaves, but now the
                                        third one is missing between 32v and 33r. IX: There is a
                                        lacunae after 38v. X: There is a lacunae between 39v and
                                        40r.</p>
                                </condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc hands="4">
                            <handNote script="textualis" scope="sole">
                                <p>The first hand occurs on 1r-40v and is a gothic bookhand from the
                                    second half of the fourteenth century.</p>
                            </handNote>
                            <handNote script="cursiva" scope="sole">
                                <p>The second hand occurs on 40r, is from the second half of the
                                    fourteenth century written is in a gothic cursive.</p>
                            </handNote>
                            <handNote script="cursiva" scope="sole">
                                <p>The third hand occurs on 40v and is a gothic cursive from the
                                    second half of the fourteenth century. The scribe is named <name type="person">Halvard Ruffe</name>
                        </p>
                            </handNote>
                            <handNote scribe="MarNie001" script="cursiva" scope="sole">
                                <p>The fourth hand occurs on 40v and is a gothic cursive from the
                                    second half of the fourteenth century. The scribe is named <name type="person" key="MarNie001">Martin Nielssön.</name>
                        </p>
                            </handNote>
